{"type":"message","id":"cc3bb99e","parentId":"c3dbf884","timestamp":"2026-02-21T23:52:29.757Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_bdrk_01RMAgUyy9QAgMcL1iXBzDik","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Initializing skill: json-to-excel\n   Location: /home/node/.openclaw/workspace/skills\n   Resources: scripts\n\n[OK] Created skill directory: /home/node/.openclaw/workspace/skills/json-to-excel\n[OK] Created SKILL.md\n[OK] Created scripts/\n\n[OK] Skill 'json-to-excel' initialized successfully at /home/node/.openclaw/workspace/skills/json-to-excel\n\nNext steps:\n1. Edit SKILL.md to complete the TODO items and update the description\n2. Add resources to scripts/, references/, and assets/ as needed\n3. Run the validator when ready to check the skill structure"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":126,"aggregated":"Initializing skill: json-to-excel\n   Location: /home/node/.openclaw/workspace/skills\n   Resources: scripts\n\n[OK] Created skill directory: /home/node/.openclaw/workspace/skills/json-to-excel\n[OK] Created SKILL.md\n[OK] Created scripts/\n\n[OK] Skill 'json-to-excel' initialized successfully at /home/node/.openclaw/workspace/skills/json-to-excel\n\nNext steps:\n1. Edit SKILL.md to complete the TODO items and update the description\n2. Add resources to scripts/, references/, and assets/ as needed\n3. Run the validator when ready to check the skill structure","cwd":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1771717949751}}
{"type":"message","id":"d0ad4019","parentId":"cc3bb99e","timestamp":"2026-02-21T23:52:56.723Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_bdrk_01Amy5zGhbeMVgEJ1Uqk1sc6","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/skills/json-to-excel/scripts/json-to-excel.js","content":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n/**\n * json-to-excel — Convert a JSON file (array of objects) to an Excel (.xlsx) workbook.\n *\n * Usage:\n *   node json-to-excel.js <input.json> [output.xlsx] [options]\n *\n * Options:\n *   --sheet <name>       Sheet name (default: \"Sheet1\")\n *   --no-header          Omit the header row\n *   --columns <a,b,c>    Comma-separated list of columns to include (default: all)\n *   --date-cols <a,b>    Comma-separated columns to parse as dates\n *   --number-cols <a,b>  Comma-separated columns to format as numbers\n *   --autofit            Auto-fit column widths (default: true)\n *   --freeze-header      Freeze the header row (default: true)\n *   --filter             Enable auto-filter on header row\n *   --pretty             Bold header row with a light fill colour\n *\n * The input JSON must be an array of objects or an object whose first array\n * value is used (handy for wrapped API responses like { \"data\": [...] }).\n */\n\nconst ExcelJS = require(\"exceljs\");\nconst fs = require(\"fs\");\nconst path = require(\"path\");\n\n// ── Arg parsing ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nconst args = process.argv.slice(2);\nfunction flag(name) {\n  const i = args.indexOf(name);\n  if (i === -1) return false;\n  args.splice(i, 1);\n  return true;\n}\nfunction option(name) {\n  const i = args.indexOf(name);\n  if (i === -1 || i + 1 >= args.length) return null;\n  const val = args[i + 1];\n  args.splice(i, 2);\n  return val;\n}\n\nconst sheetName = option(\"--sheet\") || \"Sheet1\";\nconst noHeader = flag(\"--no-header\");\nconst columnsRaw = option(\"--columns\");\nconst dateColsRaw = option(\"--date-cols\");\nconst numberColsRaw = option(\"--number-cols\");\nconst autofit = !flag(\"--no-autofit\");\nconst freezeHeader = !flag(\"--no-freeze-header\");\nconst enableFilter = flag(\"--filter\");\nconst pretty = flag(\"--pretty\");\n\nconst selectedColumns = columnsRaw ? columnsRaw.split(\",\").map((c) => c.trim()) : null;\nconst dateCols = new Set(dateColsRaw ? dateColsRaw.split(\",\").map((c) => c.trim()) : []);\nconst numberCols = new Set(numberColsRaw ? numberColsRaw.split(\",\").map((c) => c.trim()) : []);\n\nconst inputPath = args[0];\nif (!inputPath) {\n  console.error(\"Usage: json-to-excel <input.json> [output.xlsx] [options]\");\n  process.exit(1);\n}\n\nconst outputPath = args[1] || inputPath.replace(/\\.json$/i, \"\") + \".xlsx\";\n\n// ── Read & normalise JSON ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nlet raw;\ntry {\n  raw = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(inputPath, \"utf-8\"));\n} catch (err) {\n  console.error(`Error reading ${inputPath}: ${err.message}`);\n  process.exit(1);\n}\n\nlet rows;\nif (Array.isArray(raw)) {\n  rows = raw;\n} else if (typeof raw === \"object\" && raw !== null) {\n  // Find the first array value inside the object (common API wrapper pattern)\n  const firstArray = Object.values(raw).find(Array.isArray);\n  if (firstArray) {\n    rows = firstArray;\n  } else {\n    console.error(\"JSON must be an array of objects or contain an array property.\");\n    process.exit(1);\n  }\n} else {\n  console.error(\"JSON must be an array of objects.\");\n  process.exit(1);\n}\n\nif (rows.length === 0) {\n  console.error(\"JSON array is empty — nothing to convert.\");\n  process.exit(1);\n}\n\n// ── Determine columns ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nconst allKeys = [...new Set(rows.flatMap(Object.keys))];\nconst columns = selectedColumns\n  ? selectedColumns.filter((c) => allKeys.includes(c))\n  : allKeys;\n\nif (columns.length === 0) {\n  console.error(\"No matching columns found.\");\n  process.exit(1);\n}\n\n// ── Build workbook ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nasync function build() {\n  const workbook = new ExcelJS.Workbook();\n  const sheet = workbook.addWorksheet(sheetName);\n\n  // Define columns\n  sheet.columns = columns.map((key) => ({ header: noHeader ? undefined : key, key, width: 12 }));\n\n  // Add rows\n  for (const obj of rows) {\n    const row = {};\n    for (const col of columns) {\n      let val = obj[col];\n      if (val !== undefined && val !== null) {\n        if (dateCols.has(col)) {\n          const d = new Date(val);\n          val = isNaN(d) ? val : d;\n        } else if (numberCols.has(col)) {\n          const n = Number(val);\n          val = isNaN(n) ? val : n;\n        }\n      }\n      row[col] = val ?? \"\";\n    }\n    sheet.addRow(row);\n  }\n\n  // ── Styling ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n  if (pretty && !noHeader) {\n    const headerRow = sheet.getRow(1);\n    headerRow.eachCell((cell) => {\n      cell.font = { bold: true, color: { argb: \"FFFFFFFF\" } };\n      cell.fill = { type: \"pattern\", pattern: \"solid\", fgColor: { argb: \"FF4472C4\" } };\n      cell.alignment = { vertical: \"middle\" };\n    });\n  }\n\n  if (freezeHeader && !noHeader) {\n    sheet.views = [{ state: \"frozen\", ySplit: 1 }];\n  }\n\n  if (enableFilter && !noHeader) {\n    sheet.autoFilter = {\n      from: { row: 1, column: 1 },\n      to: { row: 1, column: columns.length },\n    };\n  }\n\n  // Auto-fit column widths\n  if (autofit) {\n    for (const col of sheet.columns) {\n      let maxLen = col.header ? String(col.header).length : 0;\n      col.eachCell({ includeEmpty: false }, (cell) => {\n        const len = cell.value != null ? String(cell.value).length : 0;\n        if (len > maxLen) maxLen = len;\n      });\n      col.width = Math.min(Math.max(maxLen + 2, 8), 60);\n    }\n  }\n\n  // ── Write ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n  await workbook.xlsx.writeFile(outputPath);\n  console.log(`✔ Created ${outputPath}  (${rows.length} rows, ${columns.length} columns, sheet \"${sheetName}\")`);\n}\n\nbuild().catch((err) => {\n  console.error(`Error: ${err.message}`);\n  process.exit(1);\n});\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"anthropic/claude-opus-4.6","usage":{"input":4994,"output":1996,"cacheRead":20329,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27319,"cost":{"input":0.024970000000000003,"output":0.0499,"cacheRead":0.0101645,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.08503450000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771717949758}}
{"type":"message","id":"dfd5d236","parentId":"d0ad4019","timestamp":"2026-02-21T23:52:56.737Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_bdrk_01Amy5zGhbeMVgEJ1Uqk1sc6","toolName":"write","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully wrote 5662 bytes to /home/node/.openclaw/workspace/skills/json-to-excel/scripts/json-to-excel.js"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771717976733}}
{"type":"message","id":"4038de60","parentId":"dfd5d236","timestamp":"2026-02-21T23:53:09.172Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me write the SKILL.md and test the script:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_bdrk_015nyP6JUct11CkXA4gjZVxe","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/skills/json-to-excel/SKILL.md","content":"---\nname: json-to-excel\ndescription: Convert JSON files to formatted Excel (.xlsx) workbooks using ExcelJS. Use when the user wants to create a spreadsheet from JSON data, export data to Excel, turn an array of objects into .xlsx, or generate Excel reports from structured data.\n---\n\n# JSON to Excel\n\nConvert JSON arrays-of-objects into styled Excel workbooks.\n\n## Quick start\n\n```bash\nnode <skill-dir>/scripts/json-to-excel.js input.json output.xlsx --pretty --filter\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n```\nnode json-to-excel.js <input.json> [output.xlsx] [options]\n```\n\nIf `output.xlsx` is omitted, the output filename mirrors the input with a `.xlsx` extension.\n\n### Input format\n\n- A JSON array of objects: `[{\"name\":\"Alice\",\"age\":30}, ...]`\n- Or a wrapper object containing an array (e.g. `{\"data\":[...]}`) — the first array property is used automatically.\n\n### Options\n\n| Flag | Effect |\n|---|---|\n| `--sheet <name>` | Sheet name (default: `Sheet1`) |\n| `--columns <a,b,c>` | Include only these columns |\n| `--date-cols <a,b>` | Parse listed columns as Excel dates |\n| `--number-cols <a,b>` | Force listed columns to numeric type |\n| `--no-header` | Omit the header row |\n| `--no-autofit` | Disable auto-fit column widths |\n| `--no-freeze-header` | Don't freeze the header row |\n| `--filter` | Enable auto-filter on header row |\n| `--pretty` | Bold white-on-blue header styling |\n\n## Examples\n\nBasic conversion:\n```bash\nnode json-to-excel.js data.json\n```\n\nStyled report with filtered columns:\n```bash\nnode json-to-excel.js users.json report.xlsx --pretty --filter --columns name,email,role\n```\n\nDate and number formatting:\n```bash\nnode json-to-excel.js sales.json sales.xlsx --date-cols date,created_at --number-cols amount,quantity --pretty\n```\n\n## Workflow\n\n1. Ensure the JSON file exists (create it from user data if needed).\n2. Run the script with appropriate options.\n3. Deliver the resulting `.xlsx` file to the user.\n\n## Dependencies\n\nRequires `exceljs` (install globally: `npm install -g exceljs`).\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"anthropic/claude-opus-4.6","usage":{"input":2317,"output":693,"cacheRead":25049,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":28059,"cost":{"input":0.011585000000000002,"output":0.017325,"cacheRead":0.0125245,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0414345}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771717976738}}
