{"type":"message","id":"f7d06ded","parentId":"7f49cc15","timestamp":"2026-02-21T23:54:17.100Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done! Here's what I built:\n\n**`json-to-excel` skill** — installed at `skills/json-to-excel/`\n\nIt converts JSON files (arrays of objects) into formatted `.xlsx` Excel workbooks. Features:\n\n- **Auto-detects columns** from the JSON keys\n- **Handles wrapped data** — if your JSON is `{\"data\": [...]}`, it finds the array automatically\n- **Styling options** — `--pretty` for a bold blue header, `--filter` for auto-filter dropdowns, frozen header row by default\n- **Column control** — pick specific columns, force date/number formatting\n- **Auto-fit widths** — columns size to fit content\n\nExample usage:\n```bash\nnode skills/json-to-excel/scripts/json-to-excel.js data.json report.xlsx --pretty --filter\n```\n\nTested and working. Couldn't package it into a `.skill` zip because the packager needs PyYAML and there's no pip/sudo here — but the skill itself is fully functional and ready to use."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"anthropic/claude-opus-4.6","usage":{"input":676,"output":244,"cacheRead":31252,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32172,"cost":{"input":0.00338,"output":0.0061,"cacheRead":0.015626,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.025106000000000003}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771718049233}}
{"type":"message","id":"1a373867","parentId":"f7d06ded","timestamp":"2026-02-22T00:02:40.739Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-02-22 00:02 UTC] I want you to create the following agent with this prompt: You are the University Collector. Your job is to create runs/finance/<RUN_DATE>/urls.json containing every program result from MastersPortal Finance Masters search, sorted by “lowest tuition”, in the exact order shown after sorting. Rules: Use agent-browser. Do NOT open detail pages while paginating; only collect the ordered links + list fields. After each page, append to an in-memory list and checkpoint to urls.json so work can resume if interrupted. Respect rate limits (add small random delays) and stop if you see blocking/captcha; write an error status to run_state.json. Output: a valid urls.json with rank starting at 1 and continuous. Browser actions (what it should do) Open https://www.mastersportal.com/search/master/finance Find the sort control and set it to “Lowest tuition” (or equivalent label) Wait until results re-render For each results page: extract all card links (detail URLs) capture list-level title/institution/location/tuition text if visible go next page until exhausted"}],"timestamp":1771718560734}}
